main_body:
In Article 6 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 685/69:    (a) the amount "14 750 units of account" under (a) is hereby replaced by "15 750 units of account";
(b) the amount "0 7275 unit of account" under (b) is hereby replaced by "0 729 unit of account";
(c) the rate of interest "9 %" under (c) is hereby replaced by "9 75 %".

Article 24 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 685/69 shall be amended to read as follows:
"1. The private storage aid provided for in Article 6 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 804/68 shall be calculated per tonne of butter or butter equivalent as follows:    (a) 15 750 units of account for fixed costs;
(b) 0 729 unit of account per day for cold storage costs;
(c) an amount per day of storage calculated on the basis of the buying-in price for butter applied by the intervention agency in the relevant Member State on the day on which the contract is concluded, plus interest at 9 75 % per annum;
(d) 16 units of account where the product is stored for not less than four months.
When calculating the costs under (b) and (c), the number of days to be taken into account shall run from the day of entry into store until the day of removal, both days inclusive. However the maximum amount to be taken into account shall not exceed that corresponding to a storage period of 210 days."
